for x-rays.

17:48.367 --> 17:55.641 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But they're limited by law to
only testing
working miners, number one, and
the x-rays

17:55.675 --> 17:57.643 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
are voluntary, number two.

17:57.677 --> 18:03.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, they miss non-working
miners, people who've
retired, and they're also
missing a huge segment,

18:03.683 --> 18:08.487 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
most miners, really, who avoid
getting tested
because they fear if there's a
positive test

18:08.521 --> 18:13.893 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for black lung, somehow their
mining company
will figure out and they will
lose their jobs.

18:13.926 --> 18:15.461 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: But that's illegal.

18:15.494 --> 18:20.132 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BERKES: It's illegal but miners
widely believe
it.

18:20.166 --> 18:26.272 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every single miner I'’ve talked
to in Appalachia
in the last five years has said
the same thing.

18:26.305 --> 18:32.979 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What they fear is just even
going to the NIOSH
Vans that come into their
communities with

18:33.012 --> 18:38.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
