they're the ones
that pay.

18:58.404 --> 19:02.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so, miners believe that if
the mining
company finds out, they'll lose
their jobs,

19:02.942 --> 19:04.343 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
so they don't get tested.

19:04.377 --> 19:07.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: This is also one of
the worst
forms of black lung.

19:07.780 --> 19:13.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Is there something different
that's happening
in the mining that's happening
now that'’s

19:13.085 --> 19:15.788 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
increasing the likelihood they
get the worst
form of it?

19:15.821 --> 19:21.927 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BERKES: Well, for at least a
decade or so,
the big coal mining seams in
Appalachia have

19:21.961 --> 19:27.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
