19:29.802 --> 19:35.408 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That rock contains silica, and
they mine the
rock and coal together, and so,
their silica

19:35.441 --> 19:41.414 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
dust mixed in with the coal
dust, with the
coal dust, and silica is
especially toxic

19:41.447 --> 19:47.753 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and that is believed to be the
cause of this
very more serious stages of
disease that are

19:47.787 --> 19:49.588 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
affecting these miners.

19:49.622 --> 19:54.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's also causing them to get
black lung a
lot younger than what was
typically used to

19:54.360 --> 19:57.763 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be when you would see miners
maybe in their
60s and 70s.

19:57.797 --> 20:03.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We'’ve talked to miners in their
30s and
40s who are now getting this
most serious

20:03.069 --> 20:04.036 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
stage of black lung.

20:04.070 --> 20:05.271 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SREENIVASAN: All right.

20:05.304 --> 20:08.307 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, what happens to a miner with
this sort
of the disease?

20:08.340 --> 20:13.379 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
