pay for the
benefits, and the coal company
is first in

20:33.933 --> 20:35.734 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
line to pay the benefits.

20:35.768 --> 20:40.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If the coal company can't pay
the benefits
then it shifts to the Federal
Black Lung Trust

20:40.239 --> 20:42.141 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Fund, a federal program.

20:42.174 --> 20:48.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the problem is if you have
all the miners
coming into the system requiring
black lung

20:48.581 --> 20:54.353 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
benefits, coal companies are
unable to pay,
then that shifts to taxpayers.

20:54.386 --> 20:56.889 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: And there'’s an
Affordable Care
Act twist to this as well?

20:56.922 --> 21:00.726 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
These are pre-existing
conditions if they
went to a different plan, but if
the Affordable

21:00.759 --> 21:05.498 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Care Act is repealed, would
these miners lose
these benefits?

21:05.531 --> 21:12.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BERKES: Well, not only that,
there is in the
Affordable Care Act a specific
benefit for

21:12.471 --> 21:17.443 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
coal miners with black lung that
makes it
easier for them to get black
lung benefits.

21:17.476 --> 21:22.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, if the Affordable Care Act
is repealed,
it will be back to the old days
when it was

21:22.381 --> 21:25.151 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
much more difficult to get
benefits in the
first place.

21:25.184 --> 21:26.318 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SREENIVASAN: All right.

21:26.352 --> 21:29.054 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Howard Berkes is joining us from
Salt Lake
with NPR.

21:29.088 --> 21:30.022 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
