42:36.154 --> 42:41.426 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Now, the story of a
small, but influential
publisher that's succeeding at
making poetry

42:41.459 --> 42:45.363 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ever more relevant to the
problems and dynamics
of our time.

42:45.396 --> 42:46.664 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown reports from
Minnesota.

42:46.697 --> 42:48.065 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEOTAPE)

42:48.099 --> 42:49.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN, PBS NEWSHOUR
CORRESPONDENT:
Recommend encouraging --

42:49.534 --> 42:50.501 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
UNIDENTIFIED FEMALE: Rejection.

42:50.535 --> 42:52.003 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BROWN: Rejection.

42:52.036 --> 42:53.938 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFF SHOTTS, EXECUTIVE EDITOR,
GRAYWOLF PRESS:
An encouraging rejection.

42:53.971 --> 42:57.809 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROWN: An encouraging rejection
as opposed
to what?

42:57.842 --> 42:59.444 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SHOTTS: An encouraging
rejection.

42:59.477 --> 43:02.346 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BROWN: Jeff Shotts clearly loves
his job.

43:02.380 --> 43:08.319 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But one part of it -- sorting
through thousands
of poetry manuscripts every year
-- and rejecting

43:08.352 --> 43:11.289 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
99 percent of them -- that's not
his favorite.

43:11.322 --> 43:14.659 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SHOTTS: I don't want to be the
"rejection
guy".

43:14.692 --> 43:16.427 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

43:16.461 --> 43:20.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHOTTS: Jeffrey -- rejection is
part of the
equation of being an artist and
not just a

43:20.832 --> 43:22.166 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
poet.

43:22.200 --> 43:26.437 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, you know, we're receiving
thousands of
poetry submissions.

43:26.471 --> 43:27.939 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BROWN: Yes, literally.

43:27.972 --> 43:29.874 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SHOTTS: Literally, every year.

43:29.907 --> 43:37.014 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we're publishing about 10 to
12 poetry
books in a year.

43:37.048 --> 43:45.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the math of that is very
difficult I think
in one way for poets probably to
hear.

43:45.056 --> 43:48.993 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROWN: I think I saw your
shoulders just slump
as you said it.

43:49.026 --> 43:51.028 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SHOTTS: A little bit, yes, yes.

43:51.062 --> 43:56.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BROWN: Shotts is executive
editor at Graywolf
Press in Minneapolis, a small
but prominent

43:56.601 --> 43:57.768 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
literary publisher.

43:57.802 --> 43:59.604 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SHOTTS: What time was that?

43:59.637 --> 44:05.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BROWN: One of the hundreds of
sometimes tiny
cogs that keep the world of
poetry alive and

44:05.209 --> 44:07.178 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
thriving.

44:07.211 --> 44:11.949 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And those books Graywolf has
been publishing
-- of many poetic styles and
subjects -- are

44:11.983 --> 44:14.619 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
getting a lot of attention these
days.

44:14.652 --> 44:20.358 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Volumes like Claudia Rankine's
"Citizen",
examining overt and subtle
racism, which has

44:20.391 --> 44:24.028 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
won numerous prizes and garnered
huge sales.

44:24.061 --> 44:29.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And more recently, Solmaz
Sharif's "Look"
-- about war and violence -- was
on the short

44:29.100 --> 44:31.135 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
list for the national book
award.

44:31.169 --> 44:33.971 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Two other Graywolf collections
made the long
list.

44:34.005 --> 44:40.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHOTTS: We want our poetry books
to be challenging
-- challenging the way that
these are poets

44:40.645 --> 44:44.916 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who are engaging with important
social issues
in many cases.

44:44.949 --> 44:49.654 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BROWN: Do you think this
accounts in part
for the success -- the recent
success you've

44:49.687 --> 44:51.422 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
had?

44:51.455 --> 44:55.326 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SHOTTS: I think there is
something about the
fact that so many of us in
American culture

44:55.359 --> 45:03.234 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are saturated with media,
saturated with social
media maybe in particular.

45:03.267 --> 45:11.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the idea of being able to
hold an object
in your hand, it is an
engagement, an individual

45:11.175 --> 45:16.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
engagement with an individual
voice that I
don't think any other art form
than poetry

45:16.781 --> 45:18.883 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
can provide in the same way.

45:18.916 --> 45:23.588 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROWN: Graywolf was started 42
years ago in
Washington state.

45:23.621 --> 45:27.992 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ten years in, the press came to
Minnesota,
where it found a welcoming home.

45:28.025 --> 45:31.963 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SHOTTS: Books that are relevant
to what people
are thinking about.

45:31.996 --> 45:38.102 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BROWN: The Twin Cities have
developed a reputation
as a small press Mecca and big
book town.

45:38.135 --> 45:43.174 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We visited during its annual
festival of books
where indie locals, who punch
well above their

45:43.207 --> 45:50.414 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
weight, sold their wares: coffee
house press,
rain taxi review, milkweed
editions, and many

45:50.448 --> 45:52.216 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
more.

45:52.249 --> 45:56.220 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Graywolf's Jeff Shotts says
there's never
been a better time for poetry
publishing.

45:56.253 --> 46:02.493 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SHOTTS: The vitality of poetry
right now I
think is at a pitch high.

46:02.526 --> 46:09.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think there are more
people reading
it, engaging with it, performing
it, saying

46:09.834 --> 46:16.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it out loud, saying it in an
interior way
and making it part of their
daily lives.

46:16.507 --> 46:22.113 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BROWN: And a lot of people
writing it -- which
brings us back to that rejection
business.

46:22.146 --> 46:27.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This past summer, when Graywolf
put out a
call for manuscripts, nearly
2,000 were sent

46:27.151 --> 46:28.219 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in.

46:28.252 --> 46:30.354 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's cruel, but you like to see
the number
go down.

46:30.388 --> 46:32.156 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
UNIDENTIFIED FEMALE: Yes.

46:32.189 --> 46:36.861 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BROWN: Shotts and colleagues
read every work
submitted, sorted them into yes
and, mostly,

46:36.894 --> 46:44.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
no categories, but also drew
careful distinctions
between "no, not ever" and a
"no, but maybe

46:44.101 --> 46:45.469 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
someday".

46:45.503 --> 46:47.905 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SHOTTS: You know, there was
something in this
that was exciting.

46:47.938 --> 46:55.479 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It didn't quite hit for us here,
but, you
know, let's keep in touch and is
there a conversation

46:55.513 --> 46:57.348 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
that can happen?

46:57.381 --> 47:03.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's something I'’m excited
about having
as an ongoing out here
conversation with poets

47:03.621 --> 47:04.955 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
all over the world.

47:04.989 --> 47:09.260 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROWN: You would reject people
several times,
but keep talking.

47:09.293 --> 47:10.361 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SHOTTS: Absolutely.

47:10.394 --> 47:12.096 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROWN: And then eventually
something would
come.

47:12.129 --> 47:17.334 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHOTTS: This has certainly
happened and we've
had marvelous books as a result
of it.

47:17.368 --> 47:20.004 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROWN: And his advice to those
who don't make
the cut?

47:20.037 --> 47:25.276 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SHOTTS: I don't think it makes
someone less
of a poet not to be published.

47:25.309 --> 47:27.445 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They are still a poet.

47:27.478 --> 47:30.848 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, there's publishing and then
there's poetry.

47:30.881 --> 47:37.688 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yes, those things can go hand in
hand in a
way to present particular kinds
of poetry.

47:37.722 --> 47:46.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But more often than not, poetry
is also meant
to be performed or spoken or
shared intimately.

47:46.230 --> 47:50.735 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is absolutely the place
where poetry
is inside our lives.

47:50.768 --> 47:58.209 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROWN: From Minneapolis, I'’m
Jeffrey Brown
for the "PBS NewsHour".

47:58.242 --> 48:02.913 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEOTAPE)

48:02.947 --> 48:09.954 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: This fall, tensions
around free
speech and political
sensitivities have erupted

48:09.987 --> 48:11.822 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
on several college campuses.

48:11.856 --> 48:17.128 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"New Yorker" writer Nathan
Heller wonders
if listening differently might
help.

48:17.161 --> 48:23.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, Nathan brings us the
latest installment
in our series "#IMHO", "In My
Humble Opinion".

48:23.067 --> 48:24.769 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEOTAPE)

48:24.802 --> 48:27.905 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NATHAN HELLER, THE NEW YORKER:
We've been
hearing a lot about free speech
on campus,

48:27.938 --> 48:32.243 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
yet the crucial challenge now
isn't what we're
free to express.

48:32.276 --> 48:34.345 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's how we listen.

48:34.378 --> 48:40.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Solving college's problems
today, I believe,
paradoxically means listening
less like wise

48:40.217 --> 48:44.855 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
scholars and more like
travelers.

48:44.889 --> 48:48.526 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Americans who got out of town
this summer
might recall the feeling.

48:48.559 --> 48:50.995 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Around the house, we know what
we're listening
for.

48:51.028 --> 48:55.199 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
An early clap on the porch means
that the
newspaper has arrived.

48:55.232 --> 49:00.638 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The dishwasher making that weird
sound again
calls for the usual repair.

49:00.671 --> 49:04.308 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We tune out the announcements on
the subway.

49:04.341 --> 49:08.145 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
When we travel, however, we
listen differently.

49:08.179 --> 49:11.282 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We process everything with fresh
ears.

49:11.315 --> 49:16.420 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are no expectations, no
old scripts
to follow.

49:16.453 --> 49:19.089 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Part of the problem is language.

49:19.123 --> 49:25.596 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many people get behind the same
abstract words,
and yet their meanings diverge
and harden.

49:25.629 --> 49:30.534 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What about that worn-out word
"diversity,"
which recently emerged in a
dispute about

49:30.568 --> 49:33.003 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
an old mural at Oberlin College.

49:33.037 --> 49:38.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The painting, a tableau of
several cultures,
including a black man playing
the saxophone

49:38.809 --> 49:44.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and a South Asian man charming a
snake, had
been created to celebrate
diversity.

49:44.782 --> 49:51.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But some current students
thought these caricatures
stood for the opposite of
diversity.

49:51.121 --> 49:54.825 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They made variety exotic.

49:54.859 --> 49:59.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The mural was eventually painted
over -- to
the alarm of others, who worried
about censorship

49:59.830 --> 50:01.765 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of art.

50:01.799 --> 50:08.239 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If all sides listened to the
debate like strangers
in a strange land, what might
they have heard?

50:08.272 --> 50:14.011 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They might have noticed that the
mural's right
to exist as art -- as a creative
work reflecting

50:14.044 --> 50:18.115 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
its moment -- had never been in
question.

50:18.148 --> 50:22.353 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Instead, one side thought the
mural was racist.

50:22.386 --> 50:26.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Another saw it as merely an
artifact of the
past.

50:26.123 --> 50:32.062 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"Diversity," as a concept, had
been tossed
around so vaguely that it was
unclear which

50:32.096 --> 50:33.597 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
was the case.

50:33.631 --> 50:37.902 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Travelers listening for the
first time might
not be so sure.

50:37.935 --> 50:43.440 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We expect new students to have
disorienting
experiences when they arrive on
campus.

50:43.474 --> 50:47.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yet if higher education is
really going to
be worth the name, the listening
needs to

50:47.611 --> 50:51.715 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
happen on a broader
institutional level, too.

50:51.749 --> 50:55.185 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Education, it's sometimes said,
is a journey.

50:55.219 --> 50:58.322 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Let's all make sure we hear
enough to make
the trip worthwhile.

50:58.355 --> 50:59.556 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEOTAPE)

50:59.590 --> 51:02.593 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Listening, good advice
for all of
us.

51:02.626 --> 51:07.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And finally to our "NewsHour
Shares", the
U.S. Transportation Security
Administration

51:07.431 --> 51:13.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
